<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05036c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05036c">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05036c"> 36(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> M shears &amp; ordains godson</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; St. Martin was very zealous in instructing the young, and on none did he bestow greater care than on his godson Victorius. &hellip; at the proper age St. Martin ordained him, shearing his locks with his own hands. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 87</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
